  "texts": [
    "However, ejaculate collection method explained significant heterogeneity in the data (R 2 = 1.36%; Q M = 7.52, P = 0.023, DF = 2, Supplementary Fig. 12).",
    "Population type (R 2 = 1.12%; Q M = 2.724, P = 0.605, DF = 4, Supplementary Fig. 13) or male sampling method (i.e.",
    "longitudinal or cross-sectional; R 2 = 0.08%, Q M = 0.639, P = 0.887, DF = 3, Supplementary Fig. 14), did not modulate the effect of advancing male age on ejaculate traits.",
    "We also tested whether males who experienced unnatural manipulations (i.e.",
    "conditions outside of their typical range, compared to a well-defined control in the study) showed more senescence than males who did not undergo unnatural manipulations."
  ]
}